    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Fine-grain, durable wood of the species Ulmus americana, used chiefly for ship building, ax handles, or other uses requiring a combination of strength, bending qualities, and ability to withstand rough usage.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
